ownedComment.body: A specific role of a specific Party in the specific relationship.
The involvement (role) of an instance of a party in an instance of an agreement.

A relationship between two or more parties; the parties involved are specified in terms of the roles they play in the relationship.

Something tangible that records something, such as a recording or a photograph, or a writing that can be used to furnish evidence or information (FIBO)
Definition: A physical or digital representation of something meaningful to the audience.
Comment: 1.Technical: Manuals, instructions, tutorials, procedures, specifications, etc., that accompany a piece of equipment or software, and provide guidance for its proper use and maintenance. 2.Trading: Preparation of a set of commercial and financial documents that record or support a business transaction. International trade documentations include air waybill, bill of exchange, bill of lading, certificate of inspection, certificate of insurance, certificate of origin, commercial invoice, and consular invoice.

A Classification Hierarchy that distinguishes between Party Roles according to the associated object type.
Associated object types are for example location (PartyLocation), agreement (Agreement Involvement) , Product (Product Involvement); etc.

Can be default, linked to an involvement type, or specifically agreed upon. This can be default obligations or entitlements, of specific arrangements

The arrangement type is one of those possible/mandatory for the sale of a savings account product. The actual arrangements are a selection of those offered under the savings account product.

Specifies a series of stages that characterize the course of existence of an employee relationship including five stages: Recruitment, Onboarding, Development, Retention, and Exit/Separation/Offboarding.
A specific party who plays a specific role in a specific employee relationship.
A relationship between an employer and its employee focused on enabling employee to collaborate on typical managerial tasks with its employer.
This stage includes all the processes in which employees are given feedback for their work through performance reviews, one-on-one check-ins and meetings.
At this stage, employees who have accepted job offers become part of the company's workforce. (giving a new hire the information and tools needed to start working).
A specific role of a specific Party in the specific relationship.

This stage is about retaining the worker and ensuring continued employee development. Continuous evaluation, recognition and training are crucial at this stage for sustaining employee engagement and retaining the employee.

A relationship between two or more parties; the parties involved are specified in terms of the roles they play in the relationship.
A Party Relationship is a connection between an instance of a Party and two or more instances of associated objects in the relationship.
This is the final stage of the employee life cycle, wherein the employee leaves due to a new job, retirement, layoffs, personal reasons or termination for violating company policy.

The name of the phase of the relationship, such as prospect, contracted, on-board, etc.
The period of time during which the phase was the current phase of the party relationship.
This stage includes all the processes leading up to and including the hiring of a new employee.
